# CSS/UI conventions

- Keep styling in plain CSS (no new CSS frameworks).
- Prefer CSS variables for theme tokens (colors, spacing, shadow) and reuse existing variables in `:root`.
- Avoid hard-coding sizes when `max-width: 100%` / responsive layouts are needed.
- Preserve focus styles and visible keyboard navigation; don’t remove outlines without a replacement.
- Keep class names simple and consistent with current style (`.card`, `.header`, `.actionButton`, etc.).

